API keys------

# PowerShell
$env:OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."     # or:
$env:GOOGLE_API_KEY="your_gemini_key"

run-------

python app.py                      # interactive
python ask.py "What does policy say?"   # one-shot

basic how to--------------

Open a new Colab notebook ‚Üí add three cells below.

Cell 1 ‚Äî Clone + install
# ‚¨áÔ∏è CHANGE this to your repo URL
REPO_URL = "https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo>.git"

!git clone {REPO_URL}
%cd <your-repo>
!pip install -q -r requirements.txt


Cell 2 ‚Äî Add docs + set ONE API key
# Option 1: Quickly create a sample doc
!mkdir -p data
with open("data/sample.txt","w",encoding="utf-8") as f:
    f.write("""Travel Policy
- Meals capped at $50/day
- Hotels require pre-approval
- Reimburse within 30 days with receipts
""")

# Option 2: Or upload your own files via Colab's Files pane into /content/<your-repo>/data
# üîë Set ONE provider (comment out the one you‚Äôre not using)
import os
# os.environ["OPENAI_API_KEY"] = "sk-..."         # OpenAI
os.environ["GOOGLE_API_KEY"] = "your_gemini_key"   # Gemini


Cell 3 ‚Äî Ask a question (one-shot)
!python ask.py "What is the daily meal cap and reimbursement deadline?"
That‚Äôs it. You‚Äôll see an Answer and Sources printed.
